            [name] => custom_19_309
            [value] => My name is Myint Toe and I am currently holding the prestigious Marie Skłodowska-Curie Fellowship to work on my doctoral research in heterogeneous biocatalysis at Université de Lille, Johnson Matthey and Universidad del País Vasco.

My research backgrounds are in enzyme engineering at the laboratory of Professor Victor Pinheiro (Rega Institute) with the Master in Systems and Synthetic Biology from Université Paris-Saclay and in homogeneous catalysis at the laboratory of Professor Craig Hutton (Bio21 Institute) with the Master of Science in Chemistry from University of Melbourne. Moreover, I completed the Bachelor of Science in Chemistry from Illinois Institute of Technology.

My research interests extend from catalyst and enzyme design to reaction and bioprocess engineering for the development of novel industrial biocatalysts, envisioning better chemical transformations to tackle sustainable future. Moreover, I have passion for developing highly-selective functionalization of non-activated C–H bonds via biocatalysts to produce chemicals, ranging from fuels and pharmaceuticals to commodities.
